    <p>
      Exoskeletons, or wearable robots, have gained popularity in recent years due to the rising awareness 
      for people suffering from paraplegia and the growing demand for rehabilitative devices. In November 2021, I co-founded the 
      DASH exoskeleton student team at the Technical University of Munich with the objective of developing a lower-limb 
      exoskeleton to assist fully paraplegic individuals in standing up and walking again, extending their ability 
      to participate socially. 
      
